{
  "text": "Bacterial translocation. Using aseptic techniques, MLN (two samples for each mouse) and CLN were taken. After the collected tissue samples were weighed, 0.1 g of each node was homogenized in a tissue grinder with 0.9 ml of sterile saline. The homogenates were diluted, and 100 \u03bcl dilutions were cultured on Mac-Conkey's agar (Sigma-Aldrich, St Louis, MO, USA) at 37 \u00b0C for 24 hours. Additionally, blood (obtained by cardiac puncture) and PF were obtained for bacterial colony counts by diluting and plating on LB agar (Sigma-Aldrich, St Louis, MO, USA) at 37 \u00b0C for 24 hours. Bacterial growth on the plates was expressed as colony-forming units/g of tissue. The culture results were considered positive when more than 10 2 colonies/g of tissue were found [CITATION_1] .",
